      <head>Santiago Conservatorium</head>
      <div>
        <p>The Santiago Conservatorium, or the National Conservatory of Music in <ref
            cRef="entity-008467">Santiago</ref>, <ref cRef="entity-005845">Chile</ref>, was founded
          in 1850. <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref> sought it out on her visit to
          the city in Summer 1936 in order to introduce the institution to Heinrich Schenker’s
          theories. She visited it on July 29 and spoke to one of the piano professors, and the next
          day went to the home of the Dean, <ref cRef="entity-008490">Domingo de la Cruz</ref>, with
          whom she left <ref cRef="entity-002408">Universal Edition</ref>’s prospectus of her
          husband's publications.</p>
      </div>
